{{Infobox language |name= Bozom |altname= |states=[[Central African Republic]] |speakers= {{sigfig|32500|2}} |date=1996 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Savanna languages|Savannas]] |fam4=[[Gbaya languages|Gbaya]] |fam5=Western |fam6=Bokoto–Bozom |iso3=gbq |glotto=gbay1286 |glottorefname=Gbaya-Bozoum }}
'''Bokoto''' (''Ɓòzôm'', Gbaya-Bozoum) is a [[Gbaya languages|Gbaya language]] of the Central African Republic. ''Ethnologue'' reports it may be mutually intelligible with [[Gbaya-Bossangoa language|Gbaya-Bossangoa]].
