{{Distinguish|Leti language (Indonesia)}} {{Infobox language |name=Leti |nativename= |states=[[Cameroon]] |ethnicity=Mengisa |speakers="small population" |speakers2=ritual [[second language|L2]] use |date=2014 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Mbam languages|Mbam]] |fam6=[[Sanaga languages|Sanaga]] |fam7=[[Ki language|Tuki]]? |lc1=leo|ld1=Leti |lc2=mct|ld2=Mengisa (duplicate code)<ref name=H>Hammarström (2015) Ethnologue 16/17/18th editions: a comprehensive review: online appendices</ref> |glotto=leti1245 |glottorefname=Leti (Cameroon) |guthrie=A.63 (Mengisa) }}
'''Leti''' is a Bantu language of [[Cameroon]], spoken by the [[Mengisa people]]. Most Mengisa have switched to the [[Eton language]], though a number of them continue to use Leti as a secret [[ritual language]]. A smaller number speak Leti as their mother tongue.<ref name=e18/>
Leti is quite close to [[Ki language|Tuki]] and may be a dialect.<ref name=H/>
